<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/741> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #741" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Vell. 2.8.2; cf. Jerome Chr. ad ann. 340, p. 122 Helm; Degrassi 107, 408f." ;
	dprr:hasID 741 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/740> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #740" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "This censorship is doubtful (see RE on no. 322), since Velleius may possibly be thinking simply of brothers who were colleagues in the same office and not specifically of the censorship. If a censorship is meant it must date before 339 when a Publilian law made it necessary to elect a plebeian to at least one place. See 339, Dictator." ;
	dprr:hasID 740 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/692> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #692" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 7.24.11; Fast. Cap. See Degrassi 34f., 106, 406f." ;
	dprr:hasID 692 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/610> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #610" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "The first holders of this office, which was created to have charge of the Ludi Maximi, when the Aediles of the Plebs refused to celebrate it. Though at first restricted to patricians, it soon was opened to plebeians in alternate years (Liv. 6.42.12-14; 7.1.2 and 5-6)." ;
	dprr:hasID 610 .
